title: Strong quake jolts northern canada
author: Times Staff And News Services
text: Strong quake jolts northern Canada EDMONTON, Alberta      A strong earthquake rocked the Northwest Territories yesterday and a minor temblor jolted the northeastern Canadian province of New Brunswick earlier in the day. There were no reports of injury or damage from either quake        Bill Shannon, a spokesman for the seismology division of the Department of Energy, Mines and Resources in Ottawa, said the Northwest Territories quake registered 6.6 on the Richter scale.        It was centered 320 miles west of the territorial capital, Yellowknife.
